caption: Love M2 cafe. I used to visit all the time when I worked upstairs. They have excellent coffee (dark matter) and great sandwiches and snacks. Highly recommend.
Super trendy place. A little pricey but well worth it. They have such a good variety to choose from. Love their breakfast sandwich options and their lunch choices are Devine! Love this place .

Amazing sandwiches and coffee.  A nice place to sit and get work done and have a great lunch or have lunch with a friend in a comfortable and inviting setting.  Street parking.  Reasonably priced.  In greek town and a 5 minute walk from UIC campus.
Great selection of food and great coffee!
Cubano sandwich and torta al pastor for the win! :)
They have a lot of vegetarian and vegan friendly options. Great ambiance. There is always seating available when I go
Nice little joint to grab breakfast and a latte.
An excellent place. Really good coffee, good food, friendly workers and owner, and a Free Little Library.
Just a slightly above average cafe.

How does a weekday cafe like this not have standard iced coffee? Instead she tried to charge me $6 without saying anything for a nitro cold brew, and kind of rolled her eyes when I decided to get something else. Didn't try the food, but a cafe that has cold service and doesn't even have iced coffee isn't one I'm a fan of
Bad. Burnt light roast or dirty coffee maker. Not a decent pastry in sight.
Great food & dark matter = perfect
Friendly staff, fast internet, and great latte!
Great cafe and has vegan pastry and food options
Good breakfast sandwiches and dark matyer coffee. I go for the Americano
cafe food... yummy. Fast and courteous service.
One of my fav locations for tasty Cafe food. dropped in on tues. looking forward to coming back with my relatives. this place has a nice design.

This is a great place to work and yea the food is very tasty, however the prices are a bit high. Two sandwiches here was just shy of $20 and it is just the sandwich, no chips, no drink, just the sandwich. With that being said, they are tasty and a decent size. The coffee is bold and flavorful and they have a variety of flavors to select from.The WiFi is strong and while here it never got too busy or loud. There is street parking available and there is a Divvy station right down the street plus the public trans is great in this area.
The original on Morgan  is just a little better but the best breakfast sandwiches

I went out for lunch with my friend and her baby. I liked the ambiance, it was cozy and warm. All the staffs are so kind they gave smile all the time. We ordered chiken chipotle sandwich, chicken venezia sandwich, croissant, soup and chi latte. These were decent food. I liked the chipotle sandwich. We thought we will get plain croissan but it was egg croissant sandwich with Abocado.Even better. We enjoyed food and cozy atmosphere. one asian staff gave a small donut for my friend's baby. Staffs were so sweet and kind. I love this cafe. If I visit chicago again, I am sure I will visit here again.
Cute little neighborhoody coffee shop with interesting interior!
The staff was nice! And the food was good! The green tea was also good!
Favorite coffee shop in Chicago for sure. Costa is super friendly and adorable plus he makes the most amazing lattes.
Good quick stop for food
Ordered a hot Turkey and found hair in it, took it back to the cook and had to ask him to make me another one. Not even oh here let me credit your card. Either way he apologized. Off the list........
Great sandwiches and a cute place — perfect for a quick lunch and not too pricey.
Good coffee, bagel sandwich was the play.

Friendly staff, a diverse menu, high quality ingredients, and speedy service make M 2 one of the better cafes within the West Loop. I always enjoy coming here, and although I don't drink coffee, there are many other interesting offerings, from hot chocolate to a turkey club sandwich. I recommend the chorizo burrito and the croissant sandwich and look forward to returning.
The staff are really nice, and the atmosphere is so calm and cute. The coffee and pastries are very good, and UIC students get a discount!
Always pleasant staff, good food and free WiFi. What more can I ask for? Oh yeah, good desserts too!
Really nice staff, but not super knowledgeable of things going on in the shop. Would still support the business.
Really nice coffee shop. Would definitely go again

Since new ownership, the service and food quality are not good. I used to love this place and they do serve Dark Matter coffee. However, don’t expect to get in and out of there in less then 10 minutes.  They are also constantly out of iced coffee and try to substitute “iced americanos” without notifying customers. I saw an employee making and dumping espresso into their tank for iced coffee. It’s iced COFFEE.
Staff was very friendly, and my sandwich was good. Free WiFi and solid ambience and location for those that work in Greektown.
Great sandwiches with lots to choose from! They also offer a 10% discount to UIC students.
My boss orders frequently here and they are always so nice and usually remembers his order I love this place😘
Best Mediterranean Breakfast sandwich Ever!!! Really good coffee
Very quaint, but they don't give you your receipt.
Great lunchtime spot. Extremely friendly staff.
Loved the mocha, wasn't that impressed with anything else I've tried.

Love this place. It's kind of pricey (but you're obviously paying for that West Loop real estate). They use quality ingredients, the sandwiches are delicious, and the smoothies  are the best in the neighborhood. I love the M2 Turkey sandwich (extra truffle mayo and banana peppers) and the strawberry lemonade smoothie.
I love their sandwiches and delicious coffee. I will always come back to this shop.
I lived my experience here. The coffee was delicious and the atmosphere is so vibrant. The staff was very knowledgeable and treated me like a rockstar! Thank you for the awesome experience.
Great coffee.  Good food.  Decent prices.
Good food and service, but super tiny inside.
Good coffee. Solid neighborhood coffee shop.
It's okay. Good windows. Good light. Wi-Fi. Bathroom is accessible through a key-fob door, and an access code. Inconvenient.

Great neighborhood spot that is bustling during the work week. Features a wide selection of sandwiches (lunch and breakfast) and coffee/tea. Wi-Fi available. Friendly, accommodating staff, but a long wait during peak times.
Great local foff

Decent space, very friendly crew, disappointing latte. Milk was not steamed properly, milk to espresso ratio off, and the espresso had a burnt taste. Lot of work ahead for this place.  If you love your lattes, head over to Groundswell instead.
Really cute. Lots of sandwich options
So friendly, great coffee, and get the cake ball!
Simple and pleasant cafe.  Wraps, sandwiches and paninis.  Can get a little crowded at lunch time.

This place is awesome. It's hard to find at first because it's located inside a building, but its a gem. The people that work there are amazing, the baked stuff is good, and I think I get a coffee every morning from there. The best part is that they are partnered with Ritual, so I can order my bagel and coffee while' I'm still on the train, and not even be late to work. Hell yes!
This is my go-to coffee and lunch spot when I work from home. Staff is super friendly and unique lunch menu. Independent at this best!
Great coffee and pastries. Friendly staff
Super cute place. Great small foods. The staff is very friendly!
Great coffee! UIC MUST visit this place!
Great place for comfort food and brushing up with work by using WiFi . Their coffee is amazing .
Great place. Try the bread by the counter!
Awesome sandwiches and soup. Plus they have dark matter coffee!

m2 is the little sister to Morgan Street Cafe and delivers the same quality of service and product. It is a great spot to grab a cup of coffee on the go or to sit down and have a casual meeting with a colleague or friend. I have been a patron for years and have never been disappointed.
Great place!

I love this spot. Go there at least once every other week. Bagel sandwiches and Croissandwich are amazing. Burrito is light and filling. So are their variation of coffees. Told people at work about them, and now they can't stop going. I recommend starting off with french toast  bagel with bacon and a mocha or Americano.
Nice coffee shop, a good place to have casual meetings and get a good cup of joe.
Lasagna is amazing.
Daily visitor and never disappointed!
Great little cafe, clean, excellent coffee, solid healthy food options.  Excellent service, friendly people, and a great area to relax, read and enjoy coffee.
Delicious sandwiches and soups at a very good price.  What sets it apart though is the service, always friendly and cheerful.
Really cute cafe, friendly staff, yummy sandwiches, organic baked goods. Free wifi, tons of seating, amazing breakfast sandwiches - west loop gem!
